A new version of the [[Wikitext]] gem, version 1.7, is now available. It contains a couple of bugfixes and a sizeable rewrite of the internals leading to a [/blog/wikitext-speed-improvements big performance boost] (double the speed or more in many cases). See the [http://wikitext.rubyforge.org/files/doc/RELEASE-NOTES.html high-level] or [http://rubyforge.org/frs/shownotes.php?release_id=34439 low-level release notes] for more details.

[[Wikitext]] is a fast wikitext-to-[[HTML]] translator with a syntax very close to that used by [[MediaWiki]]. It is a [[Ruby]] extension written with speed and robustness in mind using a [[Ragel]]-generated [http://git.wincent.com/wikitext.git?a=blob;f=ext/wikitext_ragel.rl;hb=HEAD scanner] and a [http://git.wincent.com/wikitext.git?a=blob;f=ext/parser.c;hb=HEAD hand-coded parser], all in [[C]]. It has an enormous [http://git.wincent.com/wikitext.git?a=tree;f=spec;hb=HEAD spec suite].

You can browse the source code repo [http://git.wincent.com/wikitext.git here], or download the [[gem]] from the [[RubyForge]] [http://rubyforge.org/frs/?group_id=5483 downloads page]. For an overview of how to use the extension check out the [[RDoc]] [http://wikitext.rubyforge.org/ here]. If you have [[RubyGems]] then you can install it with `sudo gem install wikitext` (although it may take some time before the new version has propagated out to all the gem servers).

